```
#include "Halide.h"
#include <iostream>
using namespace Halide;

int main() {
    Func f, g;
    Var x;
    f(x) = x;
    g(x) = f(x);
    f.store_root();
    g.compile_jit();
    return 0;
}
```
produces:
```
Func "f" is computed at the following invalid location:
  f.compute_inline();
Legal locations for this function are:
  f.compute_root();
  f.compute_at(g, Var::outermost());
  f.compute_at(g, x);
"f" is used in the following places:
 for g.s0.x:
  g uses f
```
It should just say more directly that you can't do a store_at without a compute_at

